<HEADLINE> Russia, Ukraine to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian and Ukrainian
presidents today pledged that their countries will promote
cooperation in a wide range of areas.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his Ukrainian counterpart
Leonid Kuchma made the pledge at the end of a two-day informal
meeting in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation will cover the business coordination on
international arena, the establishment of joint ventures, the
mutual participation in each other's privatization programs, and
the economic legislation.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will stop levying value-added tax on a
reciprocal basis, and sign a 10-year economic cooperation
agreement when the Ukranian president re-visits Russia next
February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
