<HEADLINE> Malaysian Head of State Visits Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Supreme Head of
State Tuanku Ja'afar Abdul Rahman arrived here today for a
three-day visit.
</P>
<P>
He was expected to hold talks with Kuwaiti Emir Sheikh Jaber
Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah, Crown Prince and Prime Minister Sheikh Saad
Al-Abdullah Al-Salem Al-Sabah Tuesday on means of promoting
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Malaysia have enjoyed sound political and economic
relations since they established diplomatic ties in May 1963,
according the Kuwaiti News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Bin Mohammed also had paid a
visit to the Gulf emirate last April to seek ways of bolstering
economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia exported about 100 million U.S. dollars worth of goods
to Kuwait in 1996, while its import of oil from Kuwait accounted
for 15 percent of its total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
