<HEADLINE> Mongolia's Foreign Debts Total 500 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's foreign debts
now total 500 million U.S. dollars, central bank governor
J. Unenbat said today.
</P>
<P>
He said that all these debts are preferential loans offered by
foreign governments and international monetary organizations,
which carry an annual interest rate of less than 1 percent and are
re-payable over 30 years.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government is spending 20-30 million dollars a
year on debt-servicing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
