<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Industrial Production Increases in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Continued strong demand for
trucks, computers and appliances helped increase the
U.S. industrial production in October, the Federal Reserve said
today.
</P>
<P>
Output increased a robust 0.5 percent, the same as in
September, pushing the industrial operating rate to 84.3 percent
of capacity, the highest level since March 1995.
</P>
<P>
The October strength in industry was widespread except for
mining and oil drilling where output fell 1.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing rose 0.6 percent, triple the modest 0.2 percent
in paper products and tobacco.
</P>
<P>
Production at utilities rose 0.3 percent, surpassing the 3.5
percent surge in September, bringing the operating rate to 91.4
percent of capacity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
