<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taekwondo World Championships to Open in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The 13th Men's and Sixth
Women's Taekwondo World Championships are to be staged on November
19-23 at the Hong Kong Coliseum, it was announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
Competing in the five-day event are some 600 athletes from 91
countries and regions. And they are the largest sporting event for
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
There are eight categories in the men's and women's divisions.
</P>
<P>
The world championships are the first large sporting event held
by Hong Kong after July 1 when it became China's Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
"Through the championships, we hope that thousands of VIPs,
guests and athletes from around the world, together with millions
of global TV spectators, will witness the continual stability and
prosperity of Hong Kong after the handover," said Carl Ching,
president of the Hong Kong Taekwondo Association and chairman of
the championships organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
Taewkondo will be listed for the first time as an Olympic sport
at the Sydney Olympic Games in 2000, said Un Yong Kim, president
of the World Taewkondo Federation (WTF).
</P>
<P>
"This indicates generalization of the Taewkondo game is the
prevailing trend. And the ultimate target of WTF is to have global
promotion of Taewkondo among peoples," he added.
</P>
<P>
China has sent an eight-member team for the championships,
which is China's second appearance at the world taewkondo
championships following the last worlds two years ago in the
Philippines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
