<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts 40th Anniversary Forum on Mao Zedong Speech </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The State Education
Commission, Communist Youth League of China and Western Returned
Scholars Association (WRSA) jointly hosted today's forum on the
40th Anniversary of a major speech by Mao Zedong.
</P>
<P>
Mao, a first generation leader of New China, presented the
speech some 40 years ago to a group of students returning from
Moscow, capital of the former Soviet Union. Mao encouraged the
students to study hard and render service to repay their country's
kindness.
</P>
<P>
Promoting the advancement of society requires training and
grooming of millions of talented people and encouraging returned
students to serve the country, according to Li Lanqing, a standing
committee member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee and vice-premier of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Li reaffirmed the Chinese government's policy of encouraging
students to study abroad and allowing them to return and go abroad
again on their own will.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
