<HEADLINE> Steel Giant Lists A Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The Angang New Steel Rolling
Co. Ltd, a subsidiary of the Anshan Iron and Steel Group which is
China's largest iron producer, listed 300 million of A shares
today on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange, with shares opening at 3.9
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The stock issue will enable the company to raise 1.15 billion
yuan to expand the production capacity for four projects,
including a steel mill with an annual output of 2.2 million tons
and a zinc-plating joint venture with a German company.
</P>
<P>
The company listed 890 million H shares valued at 2.63 billion
yuan earlier this year on the Hong Kong market.
</P>
<P>
China plans to list more large iron and steel share-holding
enterprises in the future.  
</P>
