<HEADLINE> Russia in Efforts to Peacefully Resolve Iraq Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Russia is doing all it can to
bring about a peaceful settlement of the Iraq crisis around
nuclear inspection, Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov said
here today.
</P>
<P>
To stablize the situation in Iraq, the minister emphasized, the
U.N. special commission should resume its work on eliminating the
weapons of mass destruction in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
He also called for an improvement in the commission's work to
let Iraq "see the light at the end of the tunnel".
</P>
<P>
As one of its steps, he said, Russia is keeping contacts with
Iraq and other permanent members of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Primakov made the remarks at a press conference following his
talks with Danish Foreign Minister Niels Helveg Petersen. 
