<HEADLINE> US Secretary of State Starts Visit to Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 17 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright arrived here today on her 20-hour visit to
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit by a U.S. secretary of state to
Pakistan in 13 years.
</P>
<P>
Albright, who arrived here this evening, had delayed her visit
for one day due to the rapidly emerging developments in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
During her stay in Pakistan, Albright will hold talks with
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan and
other senior officials on bilateral, regional and international
issues of mutual concern, including Kashmir and Afghanistan,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Another task of Albright's trip is to finalize preparations for
President Bill Clinton's visit to Pakistan, which is expected in
the first quarter of next year, they said.  
