<HEADLINE> China to Settle Demobilzed Soldiers in Winter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The State Council and Central
Military Commission have issued a circular calling on all local
governments and departments to provide jobs for PLA soldiers
facing demobilization during the coming winter.
</P>
<P>
local government are required to continue current policies,
laws and regulations regarding the resettlement of demobilized
soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The circular calls on local governments to open more
employeement channels for former soliders, and for the adoption of
measures to encourage self-employeement.
</P>
<P>
Local governments should actively encourage the resettlement of
demobilized soldiers to contribute to social stability and
consolidate national defense, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of units failing to meet resettlement targets or
refusing to hire demobilized soldiers will be subject to
penalties, according to the circular. 
</P>
