<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Switzerland Agree to Boost Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Switzerland
signed an agreement here today for boosting and protecting mutual
investments, Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was aimed at easing the flow of capital between
the two countries and guaranteeing the right of investors to go
to court in case of any legal conflict, Nabil Al-Abduljalil, a
supervisor at the taxes department at the Kuwaiti Finance
Ministry, said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
He said the agreement also guarantees that investments in the
host country or investing country would not be confiscated or
frozen in any case.
</P>
<P>
The agreement stipulates that expropriation or nationalization
of any investments should immediately be fairly compensated.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the statement said the agreement which was
generated from two rounds of talks was of great importance to
the two sides to protect mutual investments.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is also seen as paving the way for an increase
in Swiss investments in Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The amount of mutual investments between the two countries is
not officially available.
</P>
<P>
But Swiss products exported to Kuwait are estimated at 150
million U.S. dollars this year, according to an official who
attended the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's exports to Switzerland are at a low level of 2
million dollars, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
