<HEADLINE> Botswana to Sign Loan Accord With Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Botswana and the
Development Bank of Southern African (DBSA) will sign a loan
agreement tomorrow, amounting to 50.40 million U.S. Dollars, the
DBSA announced today.
</P>
<P>
Loan would be used to fund part of the Botswana Water
Utilities Corporation's north-south carrier water project, the
DBSA said.
</P>
<P>
The bank's funding would go toward the laying of over 200
kilometers of water pipeline to connect the Letsibogo Dam in the
north to the existing infrastructure in Gaborone, capital of
Botswana.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the scheme was estimated at 314 million U.S.
Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The loan would be repaid over 25 years with a five year grace
period on the principal amount at 15 percent interest. 
</P>
