<HEADLINE> European Shares Rally on Tokyo, Wall Street Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
surged strongly Monday and all ended sharply up, boosted by big
gains of Japanese shares and the Dow's opening rally.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index on the London market closed 2.6 percent or
125.2 points higher at 4,867.0, underpinned by Tokyo's eight
percent surge and a five percent rally in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Activity was thin as investors shied away from recent
volatility, but most major European bourses climbed in response to
Tokyo's stunning rally.
</P>
<P>
Wall Street was also making good progress and the Dow stood 104
points higher at the London close.
</P>
<P>
German shares in Frankfurt closed higher on the back of the
sharp overnight rally in Tokyo. Renewed strength in the dollar
also gave a big boost to cars and chemicals stocks.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index rose 63.67 points to close at 3,794.61.
</P>
<P>
The brighter trend on Asian markets overnight and the continued
rise in the Dow gave the Paris bourse a fillip, with the CAC-40
index closing 76.95 points higher at 2,772.99. 
