<HEADLINE> Travel Industry Stimulates Job Creation in World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 17 (Xinhua) - Hundreds of thousands of new
jobs will be created around the world as a direct result of World
Travel Market 1997's four-day activities which starts here today.
</P>
<P>
Almost 5,000 exhibitors from 158 countries attend the opening
ceremony and over 40,000 international travel industry
professionals will present at the four-day activities.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Geoffrey Lipman, President of
the World Travel &AMP; Tourism Council (WTTC) said: "Individual
companies, and many countries, now recognize that Travel &AMP; Tourism
is one of the most effective ways of tackling the scourage of
unemployment."
</P>
<P>
"Now we must ensure that all governments understand the
importance of Travel &AMP; Tourism and put in place policies which
encourage its development," he added.
</P>
<P>
Travel &AMP; Tourism in Europe provides some 19 million direct or
indirect jobs, or one in eight of all workers, Lipman said.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that over the next decade and with the right
policies in place, the industry could create a further 300,000
jobs in the UK, 2 million in the EU, 6 million in Central and
Eastern Europe and up to 100 million world-wide.
</P>
<P>
The WTTC has pressed the case for greater government efforts to
encourage job creation in Travel &AMP; Tourism which, it argues, leads
to more jobs in manufacturing, construction, retail and other
industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
