<HEADLINE> 1,400 Arrested After Clashes in Ghana's Diamond </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Ghanaian police and soldiers
have arrested some 1,400 people for suspected involvement in a
clash in a diamond mining town that left one civilian dead and
nine policemen injured.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today said the detainees were brought
to Accra on Sunday from the town of Akwatia, 80 kilometers
northwest of the capital, following a dawn raid.
</P>
<P>
The clash occurred on Thursday when a police officer shot dead
a resident of the town, Imoro Yard, also known as Salisu
Mohammed, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The report implied that the police were then investigating
illegal mining activities in the town that may involve foreign
businesses. 
</P>
