<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Medicine Against Malaria Flown to Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Belgium, Spain and the Swiss
organization "Doctors without Borders" today sent 33 tons of
lactato de Ringer by plane to help malaria patients refrain from
dehydration.
</P>
<P>
The medicine arrived here this morning along with doctors,
medical equipment and tents to assist the country's health
authorities to curb the spread of malaria.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic has spread to Maputo city, Maputo province and
the adjacent Gaza province.
</P>
<P>
According to medical sources, the disease has claimed 56 lives
in Maputo city and province in the past two months.
</P>
<P>
Maputo Central Hospital, the largest one in Mozambique, has
admitted about 3,000 malaria patients, and so far 350 of them are
still hospitalized. Due to the shortage of lactato de Ringer, the
hospital has ceased to have surgical operations on malaria
patients.
</P>
<P>
Luis Felipe, coordinator for "Doctors without Borders", said,
the aid was in response to the calls made by Mozambican Ministry
of Health last Friday.
</P>
<P>
At present, Felipe said, the daily consumption of the drug is
2,500 liters, which means the 33-ton donation could only last one
month, and by that time the medicine purchased from India might
arrive.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that doctors from France, Belgium, Spain, the
Netherlands and Switzerland will work with their Mozambican
counterparts for 15 days to six months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971118.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-17 19:33 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qatar Opposes Military Strike Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The Qatari Foreign Minister
Sheikh Hamad al Thani has stated that his country opposes a
military strike against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a news conference here this evening, on the sideline
of the Fourth Middle East and North Africa Economic Conference,
the Qatari Minister called for a resolution of the crisis through
diplomatic and peaceful means between Iraq and the U.S. or between
Iraq and the U.N..
</P>
<P>
Baghdad expelled six Americans working with the U.N. Special
Commission (UNSCOM) on monitoring Iraq's disarmament last Friday,
prompting an UNSCOM decision to pull out of other 63 weapons
inspectors accordingly. Following the crisis, the U.S. and Britain
have threatened to take military actions against Iraq after the
U.N. passed a resolution last Wednesday condemning the Iraqi move.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hamad asserted that Iraq must abide by all the related
U.N. resolutions in order to alleviate the suffering of the Iraqi
people.
</P>
<P>
He denied any U.S. pressures on Qatar regarding the convocation
of the Doha economic conference, and strongly criticized the
Egyptian media campaign against Qatar on the conference issue.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari Minister also denounced the intransigent attitude of
the Israeli government regarding the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
He said such intransigence was the principal cause of the peace
process stalemate, pointing out that dialogue was necessary and
useful. It is a must as well as possible to reach a solution through
dialogue such as the Doha economic conference which ought to be
utilized to reactivate the peace process.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the representation of Arab states in the Doha
economic conference, he said each Arab state had its own views on
attending or failing to attend, and Qatar entertained no stand
against any Arab state.
</P>
<P>
Replying to a question as to whether Qatar will attend the GCC
summit in Kuwait in December, he said Qatar would be proud to
attend that summit conference.
</P>
<P>
On the relationship between Qatar and Iran, he said Iran is a
neighboring state, and Qatar maintains normal relations with it,
despite some differences. He added that Qatar differs with the
U.S. with regard to its attitude towards Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
