<HEADLINE> Trade Publications Vital for HK's Competitiveness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Trade publications are vital
to creating competitive edge by taking information about Hong
Kong's products direct to buyers around the world, a leading
official of the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC) said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Michael Sze, Executive Director of the TDC, was speaking at a
reception here today to mark the 30th anniversary of Hong Kong
Enterprise, the Council's flagship product publication.
</P>
<P>
The TDC pioneered the publication and global circulation of
magazines on Hong Kong products to encourage the world's buyers
and importers to source from Hong Kong. Trade publications are an
integral part of the Council's global marketing strategy.
</P>
<P>
The TDC is now publishing more than 20 trade publications which
deliver detailed sourcing information by industry. More than 2.3
million copies of the publications were distributed last year to
qualified buyers, importers and sourcing agents worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's Enterprise, the TDC's first and still the most
popular publication, covers a wide range of editorial contents
each month, from electrical applications to auto accessories. It
has been evolving with the times to better serve its customers,
Sze said. 
</P>
