<HEADLINE> Largest Customs-Reporting Service Company Built in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 18 (Xinhua) -- China's largest company
dealing in custom-declaring services opened in Shanghai, the
country's leading trade and financial center, today.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Hanglian Custom-Reporting Service Co. Ltd, was
co-funded by several major foreign trade transport companies in
Shanghai, including the Shanghai Foreign Trade Transport Company,
and COSCO Shanghai International Cargo Transport Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The company now deals with nearly one third of the total
customs-reporting services for Chinese exporters to Shanghai
Customs.
</P>
<P>
Statistics shows that there are currently 15,000 companies in
Shanghai that help declare customs for foreign trade
companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
