<HEADLINE> Firms from Inland, HK Co-develop Property Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The property development arm
of the Chinese Ministry of Construction will join hands with a
Hong Kong listed company to develop real estate projects in
China's inland areas, Hong Kong and even overseas.
</P>
<P>
The China National Real Estate Development Group (CRED), a
major property developer in China's interior, signed here today
strategic alliance with CIL Holdings Ltd. of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The alliance will bring positive results to both, said Meng
Xiaosu, president of CRED.
</P>
<P>
CRED has thorough knowledge of the property development market
in China's inland areas -- both national policies and local market
needs -- while CIL possesses international caliber project
management skills and the capability to secure financing and to
promote business in overseas markets, he said.
</P>
<P>
The alliance is the first partnership CRED has signed with a
HK-based company, Meng added.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the eight-point strategic alliance, CRED and
CIL will form joint ventures in major Chinese cities, initially in
Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Shenzhen, to pursue property and
infrastructure development projects.
</P>
<P>
CIL will be one of the primary interior contractors for CRED on
CRED projects in Hong Kong and China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The two companies will also provide each other with staff
training, support and consulting. In particular, CIL will share
modern project management expertise and technology with CRED.
</P>
<P>
The long-term objective of the alliance is to seek
opportunities in the international market, said CRED Vice
President Li Qinyi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
