<HEADLINE> Sino-American Compressor Joint Venture Starts Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 18 (Xinhua) -- A joint venture formed by the
largest compressor makers in China and the United States today
went into operation in Shanghai, China's largest industrial center.
</P>
<P>
The venture, between Dressor-rand of the United States and the
Shanghai Compress Co. Ltd., will produce compressors of various
kinds applicable to chemical fertilizer and petro-chemical
production and oil refinement.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the venture cost an investment of 29.9 million
US dollars, 60 percent of which were provided by the American side
and the remainder by the Chinese side.
</P>
<P>
Apart from meeting domestic demand, the plant will export some
products to Asian-Pacific countries.
</P>
<P>
Operation of the joint venture will help upgrade China's
compressor industry, said Zhou Huimin, chairman of the board of
directors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
