<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Welcomes '97 China Environmental Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
sent a congratulatory message to this evening's opening session of
the '97 China Environmental Forum -- the first large-scale
environmental forum held in China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang extended the Chinese government's warm welcome to
dignitaries and environmental experts attending the forum which
was sponsored by two nongovernmental organizations -- the China
Environmental Science Society and China Institute of Human Ecology.
</P>
<P>
He noted that people in all countries and regions are deeply
concerned about environmental problems, and noted that maintaining
a healthy environment is crucial to the future of mankind.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed to the fact that the environment has a direct
bearing on the development and prosperity of all countries, and
stressed that mankind bears full responsibility for maintaining a
healthy environment.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the Chinese government attaches great importance to
environmental protection throughout the process of economic
growth, and has placed priority on mobilizing the general public's
participation in environmental protection efforts.
</P>
<P>
He called on forum participants to offer proposals for China's
environmental protection program and sustainable growth.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said Chinese people are willing to join people throughout
the world in efforts to create a new era featuring economic
prosperity and a clean environment.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng met with foreign participants prior to
this evening's opening session.
</P>
<P>
Former Australian Prime Minister P.J. Keating and former Dutch
Prime Minister R.F.M. Lubbers are scheduled to present addresses
during the forum.
</P>
<P>
Government officials, representatives from international
environmental protection organizations, renowned environmentalists
and businessmen from more than 20 countries attending the four-day
forum will discuss environmental legislation, trade and the
environment, the protection of biodiversity, and the development
and comprehensive use of energy.
</P>
<P>
In an address to the opening ceremony, Xie Zhenhua, director
of the State Bureau of Environmental Protection, said that China
has consistently extended great efforts to improve environmental
protection, and noted that the general public has been a decisive
force in implementing the sustainable development strategy.
</P>
<P>
"This evening's opening of the forum manifests the important
role of China's nongovernmental organizations in environmental
protection," said Xie.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from a number of major Western companies,
including General Electric, are attending the forum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
