<HEADLINE> Poll Showing Gloomy Future For Van Gaal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Madrid, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 percent of Barcelona
fans polled on Tuesday by a sports paper think that coach Louis
van Gaal has little or no future at the club while only 14 percent
answered positively.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one percent considered he had no future, with 30
percent answering "little" to the same question.
</P>
<P>
The underfired former Ajax manager has seen his star-packed
side suffer from three straight defeats including two in the
Champions League, their worst losing streak in seven years.
</P>
<P>
Barca still hold the slot of league pacesetters but its bitter
rival Real Madrid stood only one point behind.
</P>
<P>
The poll was taken among 358 spectators after Barca's 3-2
home victory over Celta Vigo on sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
