<HEADLINE> Las Vegas Puts on Computer Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Comdex, the world's
largest computer convention, opened in Las Vegas today with more
than 2,000 computer companies displaying their latest products.
</P>
<P>
The five-day show is expected to draw 225,000 technology buffs
from all over the world, making deals and checking on the latest
industry breakthroughs. On display are more than 10,000 new
products.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft President Bill Gates made a keynote address Sunday
night to kick off this year's event.
</P>
<P>
Gates predicted that flat-screen technology, speech
recognition, hand-held computers and digital television will be
important technical advances in the future. He also stressed the
importance of computer network software, a specialty of
Microsoft. 
</P>
