<HEADLINE> Six Teams Permitted to Climb Four Peaks in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Six expeditions from four
countries have allowed to climb four different peaks of Nepal in
the coming winter season which runs from December 1, 1997 to
February 15, 1998, Nepal's Ministry of Tourism and Civil Aviation
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Teams from France, Spain and the United States are permitted to
scale the 6812-meter Mt. Amadablam. A Japan's University
expedition, France's Dhaulagiri I Expedition and Khangtega win
permission to overcome Mt. Annapurna I (8,091m.), Mt. Dhaulagiri
(8,167m.) and Mt. Khangtega (6,779m.) respectively, the ministry
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
