<HEADLINE> Somatic Science Society Holds National Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Society of Somatic
Science (CSSC), a national organization which mainly conducts
research into functions of the human body, opened its fourth
national academic exchange meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, the CSSC will elected a new
council.
</P>
<P>
Some 200-odd society representatives from branches across the
nation will discuss 22 papers, including seven theses on the
latest research achievements of experts from Japan and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The CSSC, founded in 1987 with the approval of the State
Education Commission, has over 700 members nationwide. 
