<HEADLINE> Shenyang Health Insurance for Poor Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 500 children from
poverty-stricken families in Shenyang, capital of northeast
China's Liaoning Province, have received health insurance polices.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang Municipal Federation of Women and the Shenyang
Children's Hospital cosponsored today's charity event. The
children, most of whom are under the age of seven, now have
insurance entitling them to 60,000 yuan in compensation for
medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jianguo, a worker laid-off from a local enterprise,
received policies for his twin daughters.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, 42, said the insurance policies relieve him of great
worry about the possibility of daughters contracting a severe
illness. He expressed gratitude for the fact that insurance
policies will provide hospitalization coverage for children from
poor families. 
</P>
