<HEADLINE> Nepal to Issue VIP Cards to Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Nepal has decided to issue
VIP cards to the tourists visiting Nepal as part of a series of
its promotion drives, Nepal's official RSS news agency said today.
</P>
<P>
Holders of the VIP cards can enjoy some 10 to 40 percent
discounts at hotels, airlines, travel agencies, book, jewelry and
handicrafts shops, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 100,000 VIP cards are to be marketed at a price of
300 rupees or five U.S. dollars apiece from the first week of
December 1997.
</P>
<P>
Nepal receives 350,000 visitors annually in the past years, but
it hopes to attract 500,000 during the Visit Nepal Year '98.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is one of the major hard currency earners for Nepal
along with carpets and ready-made garments.  
</P>
