<HEADLINE> Inland Province Starts Trade Fair in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 18 (Xinhua) -- A fast-growing inland province,
Anhui in East China, started a five-day economic and trade fair
here today in a bid to promote trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
Featuring hundreds of kinds of products of local charm, the
trade fair aims to "promote economic and trade relations between
Anhui and Macao" as Macao has increased contacts with the inland
areas over the past few years, said Jin Haiping, head of the Anhui
delegation, in an opening reception today.
</P>
<P>
"Macao has become the focus of attention following Hong Kong's
return," she said. "We chose Macao to stage the fair so that we
can have priority in promoting economic and trade relations
between the two places."
</P>
<P>
Current annual trade volume between Macao and Anhui is about 50
million US dollars, she said, adding that Anhui hopes to expand
that volume and woo more overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The inland province has seen fast economic growth of more than
15 percent over the past several years. It has established trade
relations with some 180 countries and regions in the world, and
attracted some two billion US dollars of investment to the
province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
