<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Arrests 35 in Anti-Drug Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore Central
Narcotics Bureau has busted a drug syndicate operating from the
areas of Toa Payoh and Balestier, both in the central part of the
Singapore island, local television reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said that a total of 35 people, all Singaporeans, were
arrested during the 18-hour raid today.
</P>
<P>
Under what was called Operation Autumn, the Central Narcotics
Bureau (CNB) officers seized a total of 1.2 kilograms of heroin
and cash amounting to more than 2,000 Singapore dollars (about
1,258 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The television report said that the CNB acted on a tip-off
received earlier this month and has since mounted surveillance in
the two areas.
</P>
<P>
CNB!!Deputy Director Tan Seck Kang noted that the busted
syndicate showed a new trend in drug-trafficking.
</P>
<P>
It was distributing small sachets of drug to as many syndicate
members as possible so as to ensure that, if arrested, they would
not be found in possession of a large quantity.
</P>
<P>
Seven of them will be charged in court Wednesday for possession
of a controlled drug for the purposes of trafficking. In
Singapore, anyone who is caught to be in possession of more than
15 grams of heroin illegally would be sentenced to death.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971118.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-18 13:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 22 People Killed in Clashes in Northern Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- About 22 people were killed
this morning in clashes between Iraq's two rival Kurdish groups
in northern Iraq, Turkish Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a radio report from the Kurdistan Democratic
Party (KDP) as saying that the KDP shot dead 12 members of the
Patriotic Union of Kurdistan (PUK) in the conflicts in the
areas of Hiran, Ciyayiderebi, Verdi, Dolahanikin and Belek
early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the PUK had suffered great losses
in the clashes in the region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the agency also quoted another radio report from
the PUK as saying that 10 KDP members were also killed in
fightings in the areas this morning.
</P>
<P>
A KDP spokesman in Ankara said: "KDP forces have managed to
secure, or recapture, some of the positions taken earlier by
joint forces of PUK and PKK (Turkey's outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party) separatist gang."
</P>
<P>
He said that his group had retaken a number of strategic
positions and mountaintops around the town of Sedakan, some 20
kilometers from Iraq's border with Iran.
</P>
<P>
A PUK spokesman here said that their forces had been
withdrawing from Sedakan over the last week and Turkish fighters
launched bombing raids Monday.
</P>
<P>
The KDP said that it had started the latest offensive Sunday
against its rival PUK.
</P>
<P>
The pro-Iranian PUK and the KDP, allegedly backed by Turkey
and Iraq, have ruled northern Iraq since the Baghdad government
lost control over the area at the end of the Gulf War in
1991. The two rival forces have been fighting each other for the
control of northern Iraq since then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
