<DOCNO> XIE19971118.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Raul Castro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met
with Raul Castro Ruz, first vice-president of the Council of State
and Council of Ministers of the Republic of Cuba, at the Great
Hall of the People here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li and Raul Castro exchanged views on bilateral relations and
other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Castro, Li voiced his belief that the
visit will produce a great impact on the further growth of
Sino-Cuban friendly and cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
Li congratulated Cuba on the success of the fifth national
congress of the Cuban Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Li said Cuba has been carrying out socialist constructions
under "difficult and special circumstances" and Cuba's economy has
gradually been improved. He added that Cuba has won support from
more and more countries.
</P>
<P>
The premier said he believes that the Cuban people will
overcome every difficulty and score new achievements.
</P>
<P>
Both Li and Castro expressed satisfaction with the development
of Sino-Cuban relations and vowed joint efforts to further enhance
such relations.
</P>
<P>
Li added that the frequent contacts between leaders of the two
countries have greatly promoted the development of bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
The economic and trade ties between China and Cuba are
expanding and the two countries have worked together and supported
each other in international affairs, Li stated.
</P>
<P>
Castro told Li that he felt honored to visit China. He added
that he hopes to acquaint himself with China's development
experience over the past years, which Cuba may take as a reference.
</P>
<P>
Li welcomed Castro to visit other parts of China and see with
his own eyes the changes that have taken place in China.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed Castro on China's reforms, opening to the outside
world, and the country's modernization drive. He also briefed the
guest on the 15th National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party
and explained the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Castro noted that Cuba values China's experience. Li said
China's experience can only be taken as a reference as every
socialist country has its own conditions.
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councillor Li Tieying and the senior officials
accompanying Castro on the visit were present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, Li presided over a welcoming ceremony in
the Great Hall of the People in honor of Raul Castro, who arrived
here Monday for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
In the evening, Li hosted a dinner in honor of Castro and his
party.
</P>
<P>
During Castro's stay in Beijing, China and Cuba signed an
exchange of note, which says the Chinese government will offer
help to the Cuban government in preventing the pale-brown thrips,
an insect pest of crops. 
</P>
</TEXT>
