The Washington Post
</P>
<P>
-- With a promise of help from Russia, the United States turned
toward diplomacy Monday for a resolution of the tense standoff
between Iraq and the United States.
</P>
<P>
-- Teamsters President Ron Carey was disqualified Monday from
seeking re-election by a federal election officer who concluded
that Carey illegally diverted nearly one million U.S. dollars from
the union's general treasury to finance his successful campaign
last year against rival James P. Hoffa.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal
</P>
<P>
-- U.S. Welfare rules were announced in a cautious tightening
of the federal government's grip on states' ability to run their
own programs. The rules, which are intended by the Department of
Health and Human Service to fill in the details on last year's big
overhaul of welfare programs, allow states to continue providing
benefits to more two-parent families. 
