<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey, Uzbekistan Sign Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Turkey and Uzbekistan signed
here today four agreements in the fields of tourism, health,
science and technology and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel and his Uzbek counterpart Islam Karimov after their
official talks in the presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, Demirel said that Turkey and
Uzbekistan have signed more than 60 accords since Uzbekistan
gained independence following the collapse of the Soviet
Union. He added that the ties between the two countries were
going in "a better, warm and constructive way."
</P>
<P>
The Turkish president stressed that Turkey and Uzbekistan will
make efforts to further develop the bilateral relations in a bid
to enhance their trade volume up to 300 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Karimov, who arrived here Monday for a three-day
official visit, said that it is very important for Turkey and
Uzbekistan to provide support to each other as they share the same
language, culture and religion.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his gratitude for Turkey's and Demirel's
backing since Uzbekistan gained independence in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
