<HEADLINE> Computer And Telecom Technology To Help China's Aviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Information technology is
expected to contribute to China's aviation sector by improving
airports and airlines.
</P>
<P>
The use of more advanced computer and telecom technology by the
aviation industry was the subject of a seminar in Beijing, where
Zhou A'rong, deputy director of the Air Traffic Management Bureau
of the Civil Aviation Administration of China (CAAC), said that
new information technology improved the punctuality of aircraft
and the quality of service and ensured flight safety, making
China's aviation industry more competitive.
</P>
<P>
But, "The automation of China's civil aviation still lags far
behind that of its overseas counterparts," Zhou pointed out, and a
more modern national air traffic control network with three
regional centers is being considered.
</P>
<P>
Present at the two-day seminar were CAAC officials, technical
staff, and representatives of leading computer and telecom
businesses, which also displayed their latest technology and
products.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was sponsored by the CAAC's Air Traffic
Management Bureau, the Computer Information Center, the Aviation
Settling Center, as well as the CAAC Journal.  
</P>
