<HEADLINE> China Science and Technology Trade Fair Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Enterprises, research
institutes and universities and colleges from the interior areas
of China are displaying their latest achievements and products of
high and new technology in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day '97 China Science and Technology Trade
Fair, which opened today at the Hong Kong Exhibition Center, a
210-member delegation from the inland areas of China will display
414 technology items and products.
</P>
<P>
These technology items and products cover fields such as
machinery, electronics, micro-electronics, environmental
protection, communications, meteorological equipment and medical
equipment.
</P>
<P>
They were carefully chosen by China's Ministry of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), organizer of the fair, from 10
provinces and cities and seven ministries and commissions in the
inland areas of China.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the fair, Sun Guangxiang,
assistant minister of the MOFTEC, said the fair will help
strengthen the cooperation between the inland areas and Hong Kong
in the field of high and new technology.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong needs high and new technologies of the inland areas
and the inland areas need funds and market information from Hong
Kong to accelerate the process of transforming technology into
products, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wu Zhenquan, deputy director general of the Department of
Science and Technology of the MOFTEC, said on Monday at a press
conference held for the fair that one of the purposes of the fair,
the first of its kind after Hong Kong's return to China in July,
is to promote the export of high and new technology items and
products of the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the inland areas will continue to introduce advanced
technology and equipment from and through Hong Kong, he added.
</P>
<P>
Mimi Yeung, assistant executive director of the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (TDC), co-organizer of the fair, said this
fair can be considered a milestone in the economic and trade
cooperation between Hong Kong and the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
She called on people of the commercial and industrial circles
in Hong Kong to choose right items to invest in.
</P>
<P>
She added that if Hong Kong's businessmen want to maintain
their competitiveness in the international markets, they should
not hesitate to develop high value-added products.
</P>
<P>
The TDC will promote the joint effort of Hong Kong and the
inland areas to develop high-tech products and help elevate
China's industry to the world level, Yeung said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
