<HEADLINE> Inter-Governmental River Development Meeting Held In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Today was the last day of the
third inter-governmental meeting of the UNDP's Tumen River Area
Development Program (TRADP) held here.
</P>
<P>
Government representatives of TRADP's five member countries --
China, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, Russia,
Mongolia, and the Republic of Korea -- met with officials from the
UNDP and from assisting countries and international financial
institutions and signed the TRADP Project Document for Phase
II. The UNDP will provide technical assistance valued at 3.4
million US dollars to develop the Tumen River region in three
years.
</P>
<P>
Those present agreed that the region has rich tourism
resources, and decided to list tourism as a major sector.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed environmental protection in the region, and
are giving further consideration to establishing a development
bank for infrastructure construction there.
</P>
<P>
The next meeting will be held in Mongolia next fall. 
