travelers each year and over 100,000 customers every day upon
opening next April of the new airport at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
The outlets operated by the company are an example of "the
diversity we are aiming for our Hong Kong Sky Mall retail
concept," AA Finance and Commercial Director Raymond Lai said.
</P>
<P>
So far, licenses for all 141 outlets at the Sky Mall have been
awarded, covering duty-free liquor and tobacco, perfumes and
cosmetics, general merchandise, specialty, food and beverage, and
passenger services.
</P>
<P>
King Power Alpha was jointly set up by King Power, a fast
growing duty free retailer in Asia-Pacific, and Alpha, a seasoned
European duty free operator with over 80 outlets in the world's
major airport terminals.  
