<HEADLINE> Plot Against S.Leonean Junta Foiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Security officials in Sierra
Leone said today that they have uncovered and foiled a plot to
destabilize the military government of Major Johnny Paul Koroma.
</P>
<P>
A number of people including the spokesman of the rebel
Revolutionary United Front (RUF), Gibril Massaquoi and a
businessman, Steve Bio, have been detained, they added.
</P>
<P>
There has not been any official statement from the military
government, but residents near the Maximum Security Prison in
the capital said Massaquoi and Bio were taken in handcuffs to the
prison on Monday evening while about five military officers were
brought in early today.
</P>
<P>
Details of the plot remain unclear but observers said
Massaquoi was one of the most trusted officials in the RUF and
one of the closest to rebel leader Foday Sankoh who is now in
detention in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
According to an observer, majority of the rebels now working
with the military government have clearly shifted their loyalty
to Major Koroma and have not supported the alleged plot.
</P>
<P>
Bio, a high profile businessman, is the cousin of former
military strongman, Julius Maada Bio who ruled Sierra Leone until
January 1996 Before handing over to democratically selected
president Tejan Kabbah who was ousted in the May 25 coup.
</P>
<P>
Bio ran a lucrative helicopter service to the interior of the
country, using Ukrainian pilots. He was frequently accused of
selling arms and ammunition to both government forces and the
rebels at the height of the rebel war, a charge he had dismissed
as "false".  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
