<HEADLINE> US Attaches High Importance to Relations with Pak: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Visiting U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright said here today her country attaches high
importance to its relations with Pakistan for realizing the
objectives of peace and prosperity in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Both countries should enter into the 21st century as closed
partner for a better future and to fight against terrorism and
drug trafficking," said Albright at a joint news conference with
Pakistani Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan.
</P>
<P>
Reiterating her country's commitment to further enhance
relations with Pakistan, Albright said she has discussed with the
Pakistani leadership the vast prospects of U.S. investment in
Pakistan.
</P>
