Pakistan and the U.S.A., she said, have a long history of
mutual friendship and cooperation and the U.S. wants to continue
and increase its cooperation with Pakistan in the country's
efforts to bring progress and prosperity to the people.
</P>
<P>
She also expressed concern over nuclear proliferation in South
Asia, saying Washington attaches "high priority" to the issue.
</P>
<P>
She said she told Pakistani leaders "the importance the United
States attached to limiting the spread of nuclear weapons
technology" and would also make it "quite clear" in India.
</P>
<P>
Talking about the Kashmir issue, Albright said the U.S. desires
peaceful solution of the problem, adding the U.S. stand on the
violation of human rights anywhere of the world including Kashmir
is well-known.
</P>
<P>
About the supply of F-16 aircraft, she said the U.S. government
is trying to deal with the issue so that the amount paid by
Pakistan for the planes is refunded. So far, she said, they have
not fully succeeded but their efforts are continuing.
</P>
<P>
Replying to a question on Afghanistan, the U.S. secretary of
state said that her country will continue to be helpful in
restoration of peace and promotion of a settlement in that
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
