<HEADLINE> China's Non-Communist Party Ends Seventh National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh National Congress
of the China Democratic National Construction Association (CDNCA)
ended here today.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Siwei, 62, a noted expert on chemical industry and
management science, was re-elected chairman of the CDNCA's central
committee.
</P>
<P>
Cheng, who studied in a Hong Kong middle school as a teenager,
returned to the interior area in 1951 to study and work.
</P>
<P>
He once served as vice-minister of the chemical industry. He
was elected chairman of the Sixth Central Committee of the CDNCA
in December, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The present congress also elected the Seventh Central Committee
of the CDNCA consisting of 185 members.
</P>
<P>
Founded in Chongqing in December, 1945, the CDNCA now has
70,000 members from all over the country, mainly leaders of
various democratic parties from the economic circles. So it has a
wide representation and social influence. 
</P>
