<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Aims to Promote Economic Hotels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- China's catering industry has
made it a point to explore markets for economic hotels, according
to officials from the Ministry of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Catering Service Department of the ministry
show that up to the end of last year, there were approximately
300,000 catering outlets nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The occupancy rate in these hotels suggested an overall
decrease in 1996, and more serious in luxury hotels than medium-
and small-scale ones. Costumers expressed a dissatisfaction with
safety, sanitary conditions and facilities in economic hotels.
</P>
<P>
The officials noted that medium and small-sized hotels must
stop their blind pursuit of high consumption, and target customers
on business trips.
</P>
<P>
These hotels were also urged to improve their cash flow and
invest more in upgrading facilities to further satisfy the
domestic tourist market.
</P>
<P>
The ministry encouraged the hotels to set up room-booking
networks, standardize quality and advertising systems. Moreover,
it predicted chain ownership of economy hotels to emerge in the
future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
