<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chen Muhua Meets Sri Lankan Parliament Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Chen Muhua, vice chairwoman of
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China,
held talks with Sri Lankan Parliament Speaker K.B. Ratnayake here
today.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Chen said Sino-Sri Lankan friendship goes
back to ancient times. In recent years, the exchange of visits by
leaders of the two countries further strengthened bilateral
friendship and understanding, she noted.
</P>
<P>
Chen expressed belief that with joint efforts of the two sides,
Sino-Sri Lankan friendship and cooperative relationship will move
into the new century smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Ratnayake said that whenever Sri Lanka met with difficulties in
its development efforts, China would offer assistance with no
hesitation.
</P>
<P>
Chen also met with parliament member and Plan Implementation
and Parliamentary Affairs Minister Jeyaraj Fernandopulle.
</P>
<P>
Chen and her entourage arrived here on Monday for a three-day
official good-will visit to Sri Lanka, the third leg of her South
Asia tour that had taken her to Pakistan and Nepal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
