<HEADLINE> Railway Passenger, Cargo Transport Increases in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Trains carried 2.43 million
travelers in October, a 5.3 percent rise over last year, according
to statistics from the Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
The number of long-distance travelers averaged 597,000 daily,
up 21.5 percent. On October 1, China's National Day, the figure
hit a record 683,000 for the month.
</P>
<P>
About 78,600 rail carloads of goods were transported per day,
an all-time high among corresponding months. Key and staple goods,
such as petroleum, iron and steel, gold ore, cement, timber,
fertilizer, and grain, all exceeded transport targets.
</P>
<P>
The number of containers delivered reached 280,000 TEUs or 2.3
million tons, up 16.2 and 17.6 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Rail transport long has been affected by the booming highway
transport and civil aviation. As of this year, the Ministry of
Railways adopted such measures as raising the speed of trains and
improving service.  
</P>
</TEXT>
