<DOCNO> XIE19971118.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Delegation Returns from Visit to Australia, New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 18 (Xinhua) -- A seven-member delegation
from the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), led by Guangzhou
Military Area Commander Tao Bojun, returned here today from an
official visit to Australia and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Tao and his delegation met with military
leaders of the two countries, and they exchanged opinions on
bilateral relations and regional situations, as well as other
issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The delegation also visited armed force units and military
facilities of the two countries. 
</P>
