<HEADLINE> 20 School Children Killed in Bus Accident in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 18 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 children were
killed and 40 injured when a school bus carrying them fell into a
river in north New Delhi this morning, Press Trust of India
reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place when the ill-fated bus was crossing the
Wazirabad Bridge over the Yamuna River at 07:35 hours local time
today.
</P>
<P>
A fire brigade officer said that the driver lost control of the
vehicle which plunged off the bridge into the river.
</P>
<P>
The injured, most them with multiple head injuries, were
admitted to a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Naval divers were pressed into action to locate possible
missing students.  
</P>
