<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT, November 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME -- The security of Europe should be the responsibility of
political organizations, such as the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), rather than military treaties, said
the former Italian Prime Minister Giulio Andreotti here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Andreotti, whose comments were regarded as critical of NATO
expansion, said the advantages OSCE provides occur from the fact
that the organization is comprised of more than 50 countries
formerly belonging to two opposing groups during the Cold War.
(Italy-European Security)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
VIENNA -- The oil ministers of the 11-member Organisation of
the Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) will discuss quotas on
crude oil supplies when they meet from November 26 to December 1,
in Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
There was reportedly a growing consensus among OPEC members
that the quotas be raised as cold weather in the northern
hemisphere raised oil demand. (OPEC-Quotas)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Deputies of the Bosnian Serb parliament Monday
urged the Republika Srpska (RS) president, Biljana Plavsic, to
dissolve the interior ministry established in Banja Luka.
</P>
<P>
The 45 deputies from the ruling Serbian Democratic Party and
Serbian Radical Party, who met in Jahorina five days ahead of
early legislative polls, voted unanimously for a declaration. It
warned the RS president not to pursue foreign policies, which were
not approved by the Bosnian government and the foreign
ministry.
</P>
<P>
The parliament's declaration also warned the president not to
do anything that violated the RS constitution and laws.
(Bosnia-Serbs-Vote)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thailand will urge the Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum to focus on strengthening the finance
system when an APEC fund is established, rather than on
stabilizing currencies.
</P>
<P>
Thai Deputy Prime Minister and Commerce Minister Supachai
Panitchpakdi revealed this stance on his first day in office at
the Commerce Ministry Monday.
</P>
<P>
He will take part in the APEC ministerial meeting in Vancouver,
Canada, this weekend, according to the local press reports
Tuesday. (Thailand-APEC) 
</P>
