<HEADLINE> Turkish PM to Visit Italy, Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister Mesut
Yilmaz is to pay a two-day visit to Italy and Spain to rally
support for Turkey's European Union (EU) membership bid, local
newspaper Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz will leave for Rome on November 23 and meet with his
Italian counterpart Romano Prodi.
</P>
<P>
On November 24, Yilmaz will exchange views with Spanish Prime
Minister Jose Maria Aznar in Madrid on Ankara's efforts for full
EU membership.
</P>
<P>
Ankara's hope to be included in the EU enlargement process is
becoming gloomy as the European body repeatedly issued signals
that Turkey would not be considered as a candidate for the
enlargement talks.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Turkish leaders and officials have made frequent
visits to some EU countries to persuade them to take a positive
position toward Turkey's EU bid.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has been making efforts for years for the full EU
membership, but so far no concrete results have been achieved due
to some differences with the EU on the Cyprus issue, human rights
as well as its weak economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
