Cabinet Secretary Kanezo Muraoka also condemned the terrorist
attack and expressed their condolences to the victims' families.
</P>
<P>
Unidentified gunmen, allegedly members of an extremist group
trying to set up a fundamentalist Islamic state, opened fire on
some 250 tourists in the southern Egyptian city. It is so far the
country's worst terrorist attack on tourists. 
