<HEADLINE> Political Organizations Responsible for European Security: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The security of Europe should be
the responsibility of political organizations, such as the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), rather
than military treaties, said the former Italian Prime Minister
Giulio Andreotti here today.
</P>
<P>
Andreotti's comments, made at a meeting on issues concerning
the eastward expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO), were regarded as critical of NATO expansion.
</P>
<P>
Andreotti said the advantages OSCE provides occur from the fact
that the organization is comprised of more than 50 countries
formerly belonging to two opposing groups during the Cold War.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was sponsored by the Italian Center for Strategic
Studies. 
</P>
