<HEADLINE> Third Special Economic Zone Starts Operation in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Giurgiu special economic
zone, the third special economic zone in Romania, began operating
here today. The zone will play an important role in attracting
foreign investment, sources said.
</P>
<P>
With an area of about 15,356 hectares, the Giurgiu economic
zone is located on the north bank of the Danube River. As one of
the country's important inland business hubs, the area is linked
to neighboring countries by the Danube River.
</P>
<P>
At present there is one shipyard, a machinery plant, and an oil
dock that can handle 50,000 tons of petroleum products located in
the special economic zone.
</P>
<P>
The first special economic zone in Romania was Sulina, which is
located in the Danube River Delta. The second special economic
zone is Agigea, which is located south of Constanta port. 
</P>
