<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Women Form Majority of Unemployed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The majority of the unemployed
people in Sri Lanka are women, sources in the Industrial
Development Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
Female unemployment rate in 1996 was 18 percent of the total
work force whereas unemployed males accounted for 8 percent, they
said.
</P>
<P>
Though female participation in development projects has been on
the rise over the years, their absorption into employment has not
been increased at the same time, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
About three quarters of the unemployed are scattered in rural
areas and most of them are in the prime of life and highly
trainable, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Youths aged between 15 and 29 account for 79 percent of the
unemployed.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka had an unemployment rate of 14 percent in 1996 and
this year's rate has been projected at 10 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
