<HEADLINE> Shanghai Improves Industrial Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
commercial and financial center, now owns intellectual property
rights for a group of new industrial products due to the effective
introduction of overseas technology.
</P>
<P>
To develop an international market and increase
competitiveness, the city has paid more attention to absorbing
advanced technology to raise the production levels in industries
such as automotive, communication facilities and household
appliances.
</P>
<P>
Since the mid-1980s, Shanghai has established 29 cooperative
enterprises with famous transnational automobile groups. Now, the
Santana car has become a famous brand in domestic and overseas
markets.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city has introduced 110,000 items of
technology during the 1991-1996 period, with an industrial output
of 37.8 billion yuan (4.72 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has approved 8,653 industrial co-operative items
during its Eighth Five-Year Plan period (1992-1996), involving
12.1 billion US dollars, an eight-fold increase over the figures
in the Seventh Five-Year Plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
