<DOCNO> XIE19971118.0268 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Freight Plane Given Certificate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- A China manufactured
large freight aircraft was granted a certificate yesterday by
the Civil Aviation Administration of China after seven years'
testing, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Yun-8 F200 is an improved model of the Shaanxi Aircraft
Company's Yun-8 series. It is aimed at both the domestic and
international markets, said Gu Zhongchao, spokesperson with
Aviation Industries of China (AVIC), Shaanxi Aircraft Company's
parent company.
</P>
<P>
Developed by Shaanxi Aircraft Company on the basis of the
Yun-8 F100, the aircraft is a medium-range, medium-sized freight
plane with a similar cargo load to US C-100 aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The new airplane has a complete gas-proof cargo hold with a
volume of 212 cubic meters, compared with 31 cubic meters in the
Yun-8 F100 model. The length has been increased to 15.7 meters from
13.5 meters.
</P>
<P>
Improved air-conditioning and cargo transport systems ensure
that the aircraft will be suitable for carrying fresh, live cargos
and for container transport.
</P>
<P>
The life span of the wings has been enhanced due to a change in
its oil-consumption pattern, made possible by the addition of an
obstructing net.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that air freight transport in China will grow
annually by 10.8 percent between 1998 and 2015.
</P>
<P>
After getting to know the issuance of the certificate, some
airline companies have said they are willing to buy or lease the
plane, according to Gu.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
