<HEADLINE> Time Bomb Defused in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 18 (Xinhua) -- A time bomb found near a Sri
Lankan school in Badulla, Uva Province, was defused by a bomb
disposal unit Monday, reports reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
The bomb had been planted in an electric transformer near the
Udawela National School along the Badulla-Passara road in Uva
Province, northeastern Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Acting on information received, Badulla police were able to
detect the bomb which was fixed with a detonator and a timing
device.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the bomb weighed about one kilogram. Further
investigations are under way.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, three other transformers in the same region were
destroyed by explosions, coinciding with a fire caused by bomb
blasts in a thermal power station in Colombo on the same day,
which was blamed on the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE).
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting for a separate state of their own in
the north and east of the country for 14 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
