<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Island Province in South China Promotes Information Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, November 18 (Xinhua) -- South China's Hainan province
plans to further improve its communications industry, according to
Wang Houhong, deputy governor of the island province.
</P>
<P>
Wang said the province has built an advanced optical fiber
communications network round the island, which is able to convey
figures, pictures and voice simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
The province will build a public information service center so
that the specialized information networks will be able to exchange
information with each other, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
All networks have been asked to remain open for the whole
society to share resources, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Hainan began developing its information industry in 1993. It
first designed and established a financial computer system for
accounting among five provincial banks, which were put into use
ahead of other provinces in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The province then set out to establish other specialized
information networks for police operations, tourism and medical
insurance.
</P>
<P>
Wang added that the province has set up the country's first
special organization to regulate the province's information
industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
