<HEADLINE> Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League Closes Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The Taiwan Democratic
Self-Government League closed its Sixth National Congress here
Monday with Zhang Kehui elected chairman of its central committee.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the closing session of the congress, Zhang called on
the league to enhance self-construction and to play an active role
in political affairs.
</P>
<P>
The congress also elected the league's central committee of 57
members.
</P>
<P>
Composed of Taiwan natives residing on the Chinese mainland,
the Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League was founded in Hong
Kong on Nov. 12, 1947 by a number of public figures from Taiwan
province who were engaged in the patriotic and democratic movement.
</P>
<P>
After the founding of the People's Republic of China, the
headquarters of the league moved to Beijing. It now has local
organizations in 13 provinces and municipalities with
concentrations of Taiwan natives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
