<HEADLINE> State Sets Rules to Curb Epidemic Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The state is drafting strong
legislation to control the spread of major communicable diseases
which pose a big threat to public health, today's China Daily
reported.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xiaoyi, deputy director of the Disease Control Department
with the Ministry of Public Health, said the ministry is drafting
national regulations on epidemic reporting for communicable
diseases.
</P>
<P>
Also being drafted are regulations on AIDS control and
prevention, health quarantine on domestic travel and, disinfection
in medical institutions, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
The ministry, in co-operation with some other ministries and
commissions, will also set up a stipulation, concerning management
of patients with HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
A training program will be launched in the next few years to
get as many anti-epidemic workers as possible familiar with the
regulations and then fulfil their duties accordingly, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
An expert consulting committee, composed of health and law
professionals, will be established to give suggestions and provide
legal consultation in the enforcement of laws and regulations
pertaining to health. 
</P>
</TEXT>
