<HEADLINE> Hunan Province Reports Good Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Hunan Province in central
China reported an outstanding harvest of rice, cotton, orange and
rapeseed this year.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that Hunan harvested 28.7 billion
kilograms of grain, up 1.8 billion kg from last year, and cotton
topped 210,000 tons, a 10.8 percent increase over last year.
</P>
<P>
The output of rapeseed, an important source of edible oil in
China, hit a record high with 1.04 million tons, 10.9 percent
higher than last year.
</P>
<P>
The harvest, though partly due to favorable weather, should be
attributed to the efforts of the provincial government. Loans for
the agricultural sector accounted for 10 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
In addition, apart from incessant efforts to spread scientific
farming techniques, the province is encouraging large-scale
production of agricultural products that integrate planting,
breeding, processing, sales and scientific development.
</P>
<P>
Pork production brought notable extra profits for many farmers
in Hunan. In the first three quarters, the province slaughtered
4.1 million hogs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
