<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today embarked on a 15-day economic and diplomatic mission
to Japan, the United States and Canada.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Japan, Ramos will meet with Japanese Prime
Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto to discuss ways of boosting the strong
ties between the two countries, the Presidential Palace said in a
news release.
</P>
