Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) meetings in Vancouver,
Canada, the Philippines' proposal for the establishment of a
common fund to help APEC members affected by the Asian currency
turmoil.
</P>
<P>
President Ramos will attend the fifth informal leadership
meeting of APEC in Vancouver on November 25, enlisting the support
and cooperation of his fellow APEC leaders in solving the Asian
currency crisis that will mar the region's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The trips to Japan and the United States are working visits
while the Canada-leg is an official and state visit.  
