<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, November 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jericho -- Senior Israeli and Palestinian negotiators held a
special meeting here Monday, in which both sides agreed to
intensify talks on implementing the interim agreements.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli team was headed by Cabinet Secretary Danny Naveh
and Foreign Ministry's legal adviser Yaaov Bardugo, and the
Palestinian team was led by senior negotiator Saeb Erekat and
Hasan Asfour. The meeting was also attended by United States
Counsul General John Herbst and some heads of the nine
negotiating teams. (Palestine-Israel-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia is doing all it can to bring about a peaceful
settlement of the Iraq crisis around nuclear inspection, Russian
Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
To stablize the situation in Iraq, the minister emphasized, the
U.N. special commission should resume its work on eliminating the
weapons of mass destruction in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
He also called for an improvement in the commission's work to
let Iraq "see the light at the end of the tunnel".
</P>
<P>
As one of its steps, he said, Russia is keeping contacts with
Iraq and other permanent members of the U.N. Security
Council. (Russia-Iraq-Crisis)
</P>
<P>
