<HEADLINE> Funds Collected to Aid Education in Three Gorges Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- With more and more people
moving out of the areas around the Three Gorges Dam, the State
Education Commission is seeking aid from all over the country to
help displaced students.
</P>
<P>
Cities and counties near Three Gorges, 18 of which are
considered poverty-stricken, lack the funds to rebuild schools.
</P>
<P>
The commission has issued circulars to 22 provinces and
municipalities across the country calling for aid to a specific
city or county.
</P>
<P>
Forty-two million yuan has been allocated by the commission for
educational services to Wanxian, the city with the largest group
of residents to be relocated.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng also has made donations to three schools in the
Three Gorges area.
</P>
<P>
Funds from various sectors in the country to educational
services in these areas exceed 100 million yuan and 50 new primary
schools have been built and opened.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, Shanghai and Fujian have raised funds, materials,
instruments and books for the counties they aid in the Three
Gorges area.
</P>
<P>
The Guangdong Provincial Government collected more than 40
million yuan for rebuilding schools in Wushan County.
</P>
<P>
Hunan and Liaoning provinces also have provided technical
training for students and have helped increase university
enrollment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
