<HEADLINE> Duran Regains WBU Title from Malinga </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Italian Alessandro Duran made a
revenge match against Peter Malinga, reclaiming his lost WBU
welterweight title Monday in the full 12-round fight in Ferrara,
Italy.
</P>
<P>
Duran previously surrendered his belt to the South African
champion in the third round of their first meeting on July 30.
</P>
<P>
One judge gave the bout to Duran with a score of 117-111,
another scored 115-114 in Malinga's favor, and the third a
114-114 draw.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Duran, who took the crown from Gary Murray in
October 1996, ran up his career record to 44-7 with Malinga
falling to 20-4 after the bout.
</P>
<P>
Duran made advantage of earlier lead when Maligna was
stunned by Duran's third-round fine combination of blows and a
series of left jabs in the fourth. 
</P>
