<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Auto Industry in East China Province Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 18 (Xinhua) -- After six months of operation,
an auto-parts manufacturing center with billions of yuan in
funding is going smoothly in east China's Shandong province.
</P>
<P>
"The project is a symbol that Shandong is to be made China's
largest base for auto-parts production," said Zhang Shulin, an
official from the Ministry of Machine-building Industry.
</P>
<P>
The project was funded by the First Automobile Works, Shandong
Automobile Industry Corp. and the Dawoo Group in the Republic of
Korea (ROK). Zhang said auto-parts production is a weak point in
China's automotive industry, and that cooperation between China
and ROK provides an opportunity for improvement.
</P>
<P>
To support the project cities such as Yantai, Qingdao and
Weihai have improved their water and electricity supplies, as well
as communications and other infrastructures.
</P>
<P>
Engines and transmission equipment are being built especially
for the new designs such as the T-10 and J-100 vehicles built by
the Dawoo group.
</P>
<P>
Experts are confident that the project will benefit such
industries as iron and steel manufacturing, electronics and
petrochemicals in Shandong Province. (
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
