<HEADLINE> IDB to Offer Training Program in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) will carry out a training project in Panama
to help improve working skills of the country's low-income
workers, Panama's Ministry of Labor and Social Welfare said today.
</P>
<P>
Panama suffers a shortage of modern and skilled workers.
Without access to any professional training, would-be workers,
especially those from impoverished regions, are usually unskilled.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the IDB-sponsored three-year project is
designed to change the situation.
</P>
<P>
The project will benefit workers from different sectors of the
national economy, including those who need to update their skills
and knowledge so as to reach senior executive posts as well as
technical management.
</P>
<P>
The workers-training program consists of specific packages
adjusted to the actual needs of Panamanian companies. The only
requirement for workers or employers is to go to the ministry and
ask for training, the ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
