<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Unveils Cause of Worst Traffic Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Negligence of the driver was
the cause of a bus crash that killed 57 people on November 6 in
the eastern province of Holgin, according to the investigators'
conclusion published here today.
</P>
<P>
The bus crashed in a collision against a passenger train of the
route Havana-Santiago de Cuba, and authorities said that the bus
driver did not obey the halt sign and obstructed the rail.
</P>
<P>
The train could not stop on time, even though the crew turned
on the entire emergency system.
</P>
<P>
The governmental commissions that carried out the investigation
found out that the rail was in good conditions, and that the
traffic signs worked well and visibility on an area of 300 meters
from the site of the crash was also good enough.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the bus, Juan Carlos Santos Pupo, died in the
collision.
</P>
<P>
For the large number of victims, it was the worst traffic
accident ever occurred in Cuba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
