<HEADLINE> eds-Space Seeds Return From Outer Space </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, November 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 200 lotus seeds have
finished a one-month journey into outer space to return to their
hometown in central China's Hunan province.
</P>
<P>
The seeds were exposed to radiation in outer space, and
Xiangtan county researchers are now busy cultivating experimental
fields.
</P>
<P>
The county launched the four-year (1997-2000) project jointly
with the Hunan Provincial Science and Technology Association in an
attempt to improve lotus varieties.
</P>
<P>
Selected seeds from the experimental fields will be named and
distributed for cultivation in the next three years. 
