<HEADLINE> Former French Olympic Committee President Paillou Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Former French Olympic Committee
president Nelson Paillou died Monday, according to the committee.
</P>
<P>
Paillou died almost instandly from injuries suffered in a car
accident near Pau in the Pyrenees region. He was 73.
</P>
<P>
Paillou was born in 1924 in Bordeaux. He was a longtime
professional handball player and later became an international
referee for the sport.
</P>
<P>
He was elected the vice-president of the French Handball
Federation in 1957 and was elected president of that organization
in 1964.
</P>
<P>
Paillou, a former literature teacher and a close friend of IOC
president Juan Antonio Samaranch, was then appointed president of
the French Olympic Committee.
</P>
<P>
Paillou retired in 1993. 
</P>
