<HEADLINE> Scottish Soccer Player Banned for 30 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 17 (Xinhua) -- A Scottish soccer player has
been banned for 30 months by the Scottish Football Association's
referees' disciplinary committee at Glasgow on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Armando di Mello, former Falkirk striker, was sent off for
verbally abusing the referee during a minor league game in
September. After he went off the pitch he remained behind one of
the goals to heap further abuse on the official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
