<HEADLINE> UN Chief Recommends UNDOF Mandate Extension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 17 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today recommended extension of the mandate of the
United Nations Disengagement Observer Force (UNDOF) for a period
of six months. Its current mandate expires on November 30.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the Security Council, Annan said the UNDOF had
contributed to the stability of the region and its presence would
continue to contribute to the stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
The UNDOF, established in 1974, has been serving as a buffer
between the Syrian and Israeli armies on the Golan heights.
</P>
</TEXT>
