<HEADLINE> Switzerland, OSCE Agree on Judicial Status of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland and the
Organization for the Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE)
today signed an accord to determine the judicial status of the
Court of Conciliation and Arbitration with the OSCE.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the OSCE court will enjoy the privileges
and immunities for other international organizations based in
Geneva.
</P>
<P>
The chief representatives and deputies of the bureau and the
members of the commissions of conciliation and arbitration set up
by the court will have the privileges and immunities granted to
diplomats, said the Swiss Ministry of Foreign Affairs in a
statement. The employees fo the court will have a status as
international employees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
